			<div class="article-correspondence layout-item fill-pattern-light">
		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="2591">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I read Sy Safransky&rsquo;s essay &ldquo;<a href="/article/1889">Safety</a>&rdquo; [August 1997] &mdash; about waiting for his missing daughter Mara&rsquo;s phone call &mdash; the way an anorexic reads a cookbook, hungrily imagining the tastes and the sensation of feeling full. My father has no emotional attachment to me whatsoever. My desire for the sort of concern and love that Safransky feels for his daughter has at times caused me to fantasize being raped, thinking that perhaps such a violation might stir some kind of paternal response, some kind of outrage, if not simply a hug.</p>

<p>What I envy Mara the most is that, whether she is home in bed or staring down a tequila-crazed rapist on a remote Mexican road, she knows her father loves her. Somehow having <strong>The Sun</strong> on my bedside table has allowed me to feel, if only vicariously, what it must be like to know that.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Name Withheld<br></p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

								<div class="block-correspondence" id="2586">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I could relate to the experience Sy Safransky describes in &ldquo;<a href="/article/1889">Safety</a>&rdquo; [August 1997], although I was sorry to hear the outcome of his daughter&rsquo;s trip to Mexico; those things happen.</p>

<p>My husband and I spent six weeks in Mexico this year, doing most of our traveling by bus. Along the way, we received the following advice: &ldquo;Never, ever fall asleep on the bus at the same time, because you will be robbed.&rdquo; Nothing unusual happened, however, and we had a great trip.</p>

<p>Like Safransky, my father worried the whole time we were in Mexico. I spent a fortune on telephone calls, but it didn&rsquo;t help. Fathers never change. I am forty-five and married, but still his &ldquo;little girl.&rdquo;</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Karen George<br>Las Cruces, New Mexico</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

								<div class="block-correspondence" id="2580">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I read Sy Safransky&rsquo;s incredible essay &ldquo;<a href="/article/1889">Safety</a>&rdquo; [August 1997] the day after my husband and I brought our daughter to college. It moved me to tears.</p>

<p>Simply put, there is no publication like <strong>The Sun</strong>. For more than twelve years my husband and I have devoured, discussed, loved, and disagreed with it. He reads more political material, and I read more spiritual. Somehow, yours is the only magazine that speaks to us both.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Sheila Keating<br>Chesapeake, Virginia</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

								<div class="block-correspondence" id="2573">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I was about to drop a thousand dollars in the mail for a lifetime subscription when I read editor Sy Safransky&rsquo;s &ldquo;<a href="/article/1889">Safety</a>&rdquo; [August 1997]. I finished it with tears streaming down my face. But then I realized that either his neurotic tendencies (probably the reason <strong>The Sun</strong> has been so successful) or his age would get him before I got my money&rsquo;s worth.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Michael Deva Dattan<br>Carmel, California</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

				<div class="text-center">
			<button class="b b-1 xsmall js-b-readmore-correspondence" data-collapsible="#article-correspondences" data-label="Read More Letters">Read More Letters</button>
		</div>
			</div>
    
		<div class="article-correspondence-cta">
		<div class="cta cta-l1" data-url="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">
			<div class="cta-intro">
				<h5 class="cta-title alt-ff">Thinking about writing us a letter?</h5>
				<p class="cta-text">Give in to the temptation. We love getting mail. <br><span class="xsmall">(Of course, we reserve the right to edit.)</span></p>
			</div>
			<a href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor" class="cta-button b b-4 b-padding-tight small" data-label="Write Us A Letter!">Write Us A Letter!</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	

